- If the integer array parameter `tops` and the integer array parameter `bottoms` have the same length, the integer result is the minimum number of rotations required so that all values in the `tops` array are the same or all values in the `bottoms` array are the same.
- If it is not possible to make all values in the `tops` array the same or all values in the `bottoms` array the same, the integer result is -1.
- The length of the integer array parameter `tops` is greater than or equal to 2 and is less than or equal to 20000.
- The length of the integer array parameter `bottoms` is equal to the length of the integer array parameter `tops`.
- All values in the integer array parameter `tops` and `bottoms` are greater than or equal to 1 and are less than or equal to 6.